menu "breadboard: bb_ota_pull"

config BB_OTA_PULL_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-register OTA pull HTTP routes via bb_registry"
    default y if BB_OTA_STRATEGY_PULL
    default n
    help
        When enabled, bb_ota_pull self-registers its HTTP route handlers
        (POST /api/update/apply, /check, GET /api/update/progress) through
        bb_registry. Defaults on when the OTA strategy is in-place pull (see
        BB_OTA_STRATEGY) so /api/update/apply has a single owner. Disable this
        if you want to keep bb_ota_pull's public C API but drive route
        registration manually or skip routes entirely (e.g. headless
        OTA-driver use).

config BB_OTA_PULL_WDT_EXTENDED_S
    int "Task WDT timeout (s) during OTA flash phase"
    range 30 1800
    default 300
    help
        While bb_ota_pull is downloading + writing firmware, esp_flash_write
        calls cache_disable for tens of ms at a time, and consumer pause
        callbacks may hold the mining task in a semaphore wait for the full
        download. WDT-subscribed tasks (typically IDLE0 and consumer mining
        tasks) cannot reset the WDT during these windows; if the cumulative
        unfed window exceeds CONFIG_ESP_TASK_WDT_TIMEOUT_S the WDT trips.

        bb_ota_pull temporarily reconfigures the WDT timeout to this value
        for the duration of the OTA work, then restores the Kconfig default
        on exit. 300 s covers a full firmware download over weak WiFi.

config BB_OTA_PULL_MIN_HEAP_BLOCK_BYTES
    int "Pre-OTA minimum largest-free-block guard (bytes, 0=off)"
    range 0 131072
    default 9216
    help
        Pre-flight heap guard. Before the TLS handshake, bb_ota_pull checks
        heap_caps_get_largest_free_block(MALLOC_CAP_INTERNAL|MALLOC_CAP_8BIT)
        and refuses the pull (clean error, no crash) if it is below this value
        — the mbedTLS IN buffer + handshake need a contiguous internal block.

        Default 9216 (≈ CONFIG_MBEDTLS_SSL_IN_CONTENT_LEN 8192 + ~1 KB record
        overhead) so a low-heap or fragmented no-PSRAM board refuses the OTA
        cleanly instead of OOM-crashing mid-TLS-handshake. The guard is inert
        on boards with adequate heap headroom (all current pull-strategy boards
        have well over 9 KB largest free block at OTA time).

        If your project raises CONFIG_MBEDTLS_SSL_IN_CONTENT_LEN above 8192,
        set this to that value + ~1024 to match. Set to 0 to disable the check
        entirely (restores the pre-#330 behaviour). Does not meaningfully affect
        the full-heap OTA boot-mode path (ample heap by construction).

endmenu
